				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Biochar is a charcoal-like substance made by burning organic material from agricultural and forestry wastes, known as biomass, in a controlled process. It is thermally treated biomass that primarily consists of carbon and is considered a renewable resource when produced sustainably. Biochar is used to improve soil functions and reduce emissions from biomass that would otherwise degrade into greenhouse gases. The International Biochar Initiative defines biochar as a solid material obtained from the carbonization of biomass.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">生物炭是一种类似木炭的物质，通过在受控过程中燃烧农业和林业废物中的有机材料制成。它是经过热处理的生物质，主要由碳组成，被视为可再生资源。生物炭用于改善土壤功能，减少生物量的排放。国际生物炭倡议将生物炭定义为通过生物质碳化获得的固体材料。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Primarily carbon</sumFormula>
